President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama express their sadness over the passing of Grace Lee Boggs, an author, philosopher, and activist. They highlight her dedication to serving and advocating for the rights of others, from her community activism in Detroit to her leadership in the civil rights movement. As a child of Chinese immigrants and a woman, Boggs overcame barriers and understood the power of community organizing to bring about change. Her passion for helping others and rejuvenating communities will continue to inspire future generations. The Obamas extend their thoughts and prayers to Boggs' family and loved ones.